    {
      "logical_unit_id": "MD12648_lu31",
      "document_id": "MD12648",
      "title": "Withdrawn",
      "text": "Withdrawn\nThe CyM-CC portal has the capability for switching / interchanging the user within a bank\nacross the country (user manual is attached for ready reference). If a CC is unable to\nreport daily transactions in CyM Portal due to connectivity or other technical issues in that\nparticular CC, the Back Office (BO) Administrator of the bank can map the user-id of\nanother CC of that bank to the CC having connectivity issues for reporting of daily\ntransactions. On completion of the transactions the user rights shall be restored to the\noriginal CC. This functionality would help CCs in avoiding delayed reporting and\nconsequent punitive action. CC holding banks are advised to include this aspect in their\nCC Business Continuity Plan (BCP).",
      "node_type": "section",
      "level": 3,
      "page_range": [
        5
      ],
      "hierarchy_node_ids": [
        "MD12648_n31"
