    {
      "logical_unit_id": "MD12648_lu35",
      "document_id": "MD12648",
      "title": "6.2.1 Given the business continuity capability provided by the CyM (see paragraph 5",
      "text": "6.2.1 Given the business continuity capability provided by the CyM (see paragraph 5\nabove), there should ordinarily be no occasion for banks to request for reconsideration of\nthe Reserve Bank's decision. However, representations, if any, on account of genuine\ndifficulties faced by currency chests especially in hilly / remote areas and those affected\nby natural calamities, etc., may be made to the Regional Director / Chief General Manager\n/ Officer-in-Charge of the Regional Office concerned through the Head / Controlling office\nof the bank within a month from the date of debit.",
      "node_type": "clause",
      "level": 5,
